        "body": "## Description\n\nI found two bugs in the Mongoose codebase:\n\n### Bug 1: Typo in Text Search Operator Error Path\n**File**: `lib/schema/operators/text.js` (line 31)\n\nThe error path for `$caseSensitive` is incorrectly set to `$castSensitive` (missing 'e' in 'case'). This causes incorrect error messages when casting the `$caseSensitive` field fails.\n\n**Current code:**\n```javascript\nif (val.$caseSensitive != null) {\n  val.$caseSensitive = castBoolean(val.$caseSensitive,\n    path + '.$castSensitive');  // ❌ Typo: should be '$caseSensitive'\n}\n```\n\n**Should be:**\n```javascript\nif (val.$caseSensitive != null) {\n  val.$caseSensitive = castBoolean(val.$caseSensitive,\n    path + '.$caseSensitive');  // ✅ Correct\n}\n```\n\n### Bug 2: Incorrect Variable in Double Casting\n**File**: `lib/cast/double.js` (line 37)\n\nWhen casting objects with `valueOf()` or `toString()` methods, the code extracts the string value into `tempVal` but then incorrectly passes the original object `val` to `BSON.Double.fromString()`.\n\n**Current code:**\n```javascript\n} else if (typeof val === 'object') {\n  const tempVal = val.valueOf() ?? val.toString();\n  if (typeof tempVal === 'string') {\n    try {\n      coercedVal = BSON.Double.fromString(val);  // ❌ Should use tempVal\n      return coercedVal;\n    } catch {\n      assert.ok(false);\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Should be:**\n```javascript\n} else if (typeof val === 'object') {\n  const tempVal = val.valueOf() ?? val.toString();\n  if (typeof tempVal === 'string') {\n    try {\n      coercedVal = BSON.Double.fromString(tempVal);  // ✅ Correct\n      return coercedVal;\n    } catch {\n      assert.ok(false);\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Impact\n- **Bug 1**: Users see confusing error messages with the wrong field name (`$castSensitive` instead of `$caseSensitive`)\n- **Bug 2**: Objects with `valueOf()`/`toString()` methods may not be cast correctly to doubles\n\n## Testing\nAll existing tests pass (3968 passing) with these fixes applied.\n\nI have a PR ready with the fixes.",
